OL,3,CLabour turmoil continues as Streeting
OL,4,Cmulls leadership challenge
OL,6,FEfforts to lever Sir Keir out of
OL,7,FDowning Street appeared to stall on
OL,8,FWednesday, with no further ministerial
OL,9,Fresignations or backbench calls for
OL,10,Fhis resignation as Westminster turned
OL,11,Fits attention to the King's Speech.
OL,13,FBut the morning saw Labour's trade
OL,14,Funion backers pull their support for
OL,15,FSir Keir, while Mr Streeting's team
OL,16,Ffailed to deny claims he was poised to
OL,17,Fquit.
OL,19,FIf he mounts a challenge, Mr Streeting
OL,20,Fwill need the support of 81 Labour MPs
OL,21,Fto begin a formal contest.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
